               <scopecontent id="aspace_7907be8ac865f5b98222b94cc4aadbde">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Folder five contains an undated greeting card sent to Michael Antisdale and Mark Melanson from Holly Abery-Wetstone, a member of the Town Council of West Hartford. In the card, Abery-Wetstone commends the two men for their courage in demanding equal treatment for couples of all kinds. Further, she notes her intention to draft a new alternative rate reduction and propose it to the full council at its meeting on July 14. The folder also contains a United States Postal Service receipt indicating that Mr. Antisdale sent the card to his attorney, Maureen Murphy, as a piece of evidence in the civil suit.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
